reviews.review_text: Too much pressure for the boys The boys in first set were ok . . .on their collective way, second set got lazy and sloppy.  Great set list; less than memorable playin.

Typical West coast show Nice sound! the Music plays the band! Except for the first 1/4 of Hell in a Bucket. Board issues. Great first set. Vocals fairly strong! Keys stand out which is a plus for me. Second set is flowing but does lack some intensity.Except for Bobby's denile when Brent askes him to be his girl in Good Lovin'LOL "NO WAY" But over all a beautiful show.Shakespeer must be High
